description: A crudely built hunk of iron shaped into an axe with a solid wooden handle. Deals chopping damage
name: Crude War Axe

description: A round wooden shield held together by crudely hammered iron strips and rivets. Boasts decent elemental resistances besides fire.
name: Wooden Round Shield

description: A massive curved sword with great reach and heft. Deals slashing damage that also applies minor blood loss to targets
name: Iron Odachi

description: A small hatchet made of iron with a sturdy wooden handle. Primarily useful for cutting wood to size, though it can be used as a weapon in a pinch.
name: Iron Hatchet

description: A mace with a multitude of spakes arranged in the shape of a rippling star. Deals blunt damage and causes tiny amounts of blood loss buildup.
name: Iron Morningstar

description: A thin iron shield emblazened with the crest of the 7 gods. Boasts decent resistance to physical attacks and flames but a weakness to electricity.
name: Iron Kite Shield

description: A holy symbol wrapped up in soft linnens. Used to channel and cast faith-based magic.
name: Faded Cloth Talisman

description: A short curved iron blade. Deals slashing damage.
name: Iron Scimitar

description: A long needle-like blade with a hard point and sharpened edge. Primarily used for thrusting, though it is capable of slashing.
name: Iron Estoc

description: A small wooden wand engraved with magical runes. Used to channel and cast intelligence-based magic.
name: Wooden Wand

description: A candle wrapped in linnen and composed of various natural ingredients that acts as a channel to cast arcane-based magic.
name: Arcane Candle

description: A straight sword made of iron. Well balanced and sturdy, it would be fit for a king were it not for its simple construction.
name: Iron Longsword

description: A large shield that stands as high as the sternum of most men. With enough strength, this shield can be wielded like any other and provides ample protection from most sources besides fire.
name: Wooden Towershield

description: A curved iron blade with a hooked point primarily used to gut and skin animals. Though not its primary use, it can make a suitable weapon.
name: Iron Dagger

description: A wooden bow primarily used for hunting game. It requires moderate strength and agility to wield and can fire arrows.
name: Hunting Bow

description: A short iron blade fit for slashing and thrusting.
name: Iron Shortsword

description: A short spear with a hammered iron tip. Short for a spear, it still outranges most weapons.
name: Iron Short Spear

description: A long iron spear with a hammered iron tip. Its length demands that it be held with both hands.
name: Iron Spear

description: A fist weapon composed of thick layers of leather studded with iron rivets. This weapon has pitiful range but is light, fast, and deals decent blunt damage.
name: Iron Reinforced Caestus

description: A large thick sword made of iron. Its ample weight and length demand it be held with both hands.
name: Iron Bastard Sword

description: A massive mace with a devastating head designed to crack armor and tough scales like glass. Requires ample strength and both hands to wield.
name: Iron Great Mace

description: A large slender sword made of iron fit for slashing and thrusting. Its ample weight and length demand it be held with both hands.
name: Iron Claymore

description: A veritable slab of iron shaped into an axe. Deals immense chopping damage given its modest materials. Requires ample strength and two hands to wield.
name: Iron Great Axe

description: A large spear originally meant for horseback jousting. Its ample weight and length demand it be held with both hands.
name: Iron Lance

description: A versitile weapon combining an axe and a spear into one weapon. Its ample length requires two hands to wield.
name: Iron Halberd

description: A long weapon with the head of a hammer and the point of a spear. Excellent at cracking through tough armor. Its ample length requires two hands to wield.
name: Iron Polehammer

description: A wooden longbow with iron reinforcements that provide increased draw weight, and therefore, higher damage and range than a traditional bow.
name: Iron Reinforced Longbow

description: A compound bow primarily composed of wood with iron mechanisms and extra strings to ease the strength required to draw.
name: Iron Reinforced Compound Bow

description: A wooden compound bow with iron mechanisms and extra strings that help to ease the strength required to draw it.
name: Wooden Compound Bow

description: A massive wooden bow. It's size demands great strength to draw and fire.
name: Wooden Great Bow

description: A wooden crossbow with iron mechanisms to hold the string in place before firing. Requires ample time to reload making followup shots difficult to impossible.
name: Wooden Crossbow

description: A wooden crossbow with iron reinforcements. Requires ample time to reload making followup shots difficult to impossible.
name: Iron Reinforced Crossbow

description: A wooden crossbow with an intricate iron mechanism that allows for it to be loaded with with less strength than other crossbows.
name: Iron Pulley Crossbow

description: An curved iron blade with a razor sharp edge. Deals slashing damage and minor bleed buildup.
name: Iron Katana
